research/history/logs/agent_round_0070.stdout.log:598:research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0067.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The stable small-EF recovery path should continue by lowering K one step further on the known working `lowrank_gated_residual` recipe, so `K=48`, `EF=8` is the next conservative point to test whether lower-K exploration can proceed without reintroducing instability.","summary":"Keep the recovery anchor fixed on `lowrank_gated_residual`, `EF=8`, `signum`, and `LR=1.6e-3`, and change only `K` from `56` to `48` in proxy. This maintains crash-recovery discipline while continuing the required lower-K mapping on the safest available family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is still recovery-mode work rather than a true stagnation-breaking architecture pivot, but it matches the active runtime override and minimizes risk after consecutive crashes. The main downside is likely another non-improving result, but it preserves a clean signal and a stable anchor for later rounds.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"K","value":"48"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 67 remains in stability-first recovery mode and keeps the known working `lowrank_gated_residual` small-EF recipe fixed except for lowering `K` from `56` to `48`.","This continues lower-K exploration under the runtime crash-recovery override rather than opening another architecture branch while the system is unstable.","If `K=48`, `EF=8` runs cleanly, it becomes the next recovery anchor for any further lower-K steps; if it crashes, treat the failure as broader runtime fragility rather than a verdict on the family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=48`, `EF=8` runs cleanly, continue the recovery sweep to `K=40` before leaving crash-recovery mode.","If `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=48`, `EF=8` crashes, use an even more conservative parameter-only recovery move on the same family instead of any architecture or code change."],"primary_variable":"k"}
