research/history/logs/agent_round_0093.stdout.log:4559:research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0042.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After multiple rounds dominated by gated-local tuning and unresolved crash recovery, the most informative next move is to advance an already-incubating alternate family rather than spend another round near the current gated anchor. A clean `topk` K=128 proxy run under the current strongest gated training regime tests whether simpler support selection benefits more from the improved optimizer and regularization settings than it did in earlier comparisons.","summary":"Run a fresh `topk` K=128 proxy mainline comparison using the current strongest signum gated regime to see whether the improved training setup materially closes the quality gap for the incubating top-k family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This is a better use of the round than another gated-adjacent parameter tweak because the search has gone too long without advancing a distinct family, and `topk` already has working runs that can cleanly absorb the stronger regime. The main risk is that top-k remains well behind gated on FVU, but that negative result is still useful because it would retire a lingering incumbent alternative and narrow future exploration toward more novel architectures.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The search has now gone eight rounds without advancing a new family, so architecture exploration should take priority over more local gated tuning.","`topk` remains incubating with older K=128 proxy evidence taken under weaker regimes, so it deserves one clean comparison against the current strongest training setup before being retired or promoted.","This round keeps the regime fixed to the current gated anchor settings and changes only architecture, giving a direct read on whether simpler global top-k selection benefits from the newer training recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `topk` improves materially over its prior proxy results and is competitive with gated at K=128, promote it to full and begin family-specific stabilization from this stronger anchor.","If `topk` runs normally but remains clearly worse than gated, retire it from near-term focus and move to a more expressive new architecture family.","If `topk` is still worse on FVU but shows meaningfully better runtime or memory behavior, keep it alive as a cost-quality tradeoff family rather than a main quality contender."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0093.stdout.log:4596:research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0050.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Crash recovery mode requires returning to the best known working gated path with only a minor parameter adjustment. The safest informative move is to reuse the strongest stable recipe and probe the adjacent lower-K point `K=64`, which is already a validated Pareto setting and avoids the blocked architecture-code path entirely.","summary":"Run a gated proxy stabilization pass on the current best EF=16 signum configuration with `K=64`, keeping LR=1.6e-3 and AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows crash-recovery constraints exactly by avoiding code edits and using the strongest validated family with one small parameter change. The main risk is limited novelty because K=64 is already known, but this is the least risky way to recover a clean signal after consecutive architecture-path crashes.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"64"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Crash recovery mode requires a param-only round on the current best working configuration, so this round returns to the stable gated recipe.","The `factorized_topk` path has now crashed repeatedly for implementation-layer reasons, so it should not be touched again until session stability is re-established.","Using gated K=64 preserves the strongest known architecture and training regime while testing a previously healthy lower-cost Pareto point."],"next_hypotheses":["If the K=64 proxy run is healthy and matches its prior behavior, keep using the gated family for recovery until crashes stop.","If K=64 regresses unexpectedly under the same stable regime, return to the exact K=128 anchor on the next round to separate runtime noise from configuration effects.","If stability is restored after this round, resume broader exploration only with a clear implementation plan that avoids the recent factorized-topk registration failure mode."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0093.stdout.log:4603:research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0032.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Crash recovery mode requires returning to the best known working family and making only a small stable parameter change. The recent lowrank_gated_residual sweeps showed that higher LR, added aux pressure, and larger EF all regress at K=128, so the clean remaining stability-oriented probe is to reduce only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 32 to 16 on the same winning signum recipe and test whether the family is over-parameterized at the anchor.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass for `lowrank_gated_residual` at K=128 with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=16`, holding architecture, optimizer, LR, aux, and batch settings fixed. This is a param-only recovery round on the best working configuration, aimed at checking whether a smaller residual dictionary improves stability or quality while also reducing cost.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows crash recovery mode by avoiding code edits and new architectures, and it stays on the strongest proven family with a single minor parameter adjustment. The choice also matches the remaining untested low-risk branch after the EF=48, LR, and aux probes all regressed.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Crash recovery mode forced a return to param-only search on the best working family, `lowrank_gated_residual`, with no code edits.","After regressions from higher LR, nonzero aux, and larger EF, the remaining low-risk probe is to reduce `EXPANSION_FACTOR` below the current EF=32 default at K=128.","This round also tests whether the winning family can retain anchor quality with lower dictionary capacity and better cost/stability characteristics."],"next_hypotheses":["If `EXPANSION_FACTOR=16` improves proxy FVU or holds quality with better runtime, promote it to full and then compare the same EF at K=64.","If EF=16 is flat or worse, keep EF=32 as the mainline default and continue crash recovery with another minor param-only probe such as `EXPANSION_FACTOR=4` rather than changing architecture.","If EF=16 improves throughput materially but loses only a little quality, consider it as a Pareto-strengthening cost point even if it does not beat the best K=128 FVU."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
